Open for research.</p></accessrestrict><scopecontent id="aspace_078d51597b64fee2bc9e9f9caf0a0ea5"><head>Scope and Contents</head><p>The letters appear to be to and from a couple of other slave merchants, Mr. M. Hooker and Mrs John D. Hondren &amp; Bros; various locations e.g. Raymond, Bovina, Columbus Georgia, Petersburg, Richmond, Vicksburg. Some correspondence relates to the death and last will of Elysbeth Cockvill, Luther M. Sanford, and Julia A. Claggett (1837 onward) by A. M. Boyd from Australia - unclear if related to slave purchase/inheritance.</p></scopecontent></c></c></dsc>
